    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-12-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-12-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="123"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d123">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.811/166.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American National Red Cross</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-12-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 11, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Gentlemen</hi>: There is enclosed herewith for your
                    information copies of despatch No. 424 of October 28, 1914, from Peking, and of
                    its enclosures, relating to flood conditions in the Provinces of Kiangsu and
                    Anhui in China and the need for beginning work on the Huai River conservancy
                    project. In acknowledging receipt to the Minister at Peking of this despatch the
                    Department called attention to its No. 197 of November 13, 1914, transmitting
                    copies of a letter from you to the Department, dated November 10, 1914, and from
                    you to the Chinese Minister here, dated October 31, 1914, showing the situation
                    with reference to the proposed conservancy loan.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
